<div><h3>HIST 217 - Reconstruction: America after the Civil War, 1865-1877 </h3>  <hr>Examines American history in the post-Civil War period, from 1865 to 1877, a period of national redefinition and political and social experimentation. Explores how Americans struggled with the consequences of the Civil War and emancipation. Grounds students in the historical literature of the Reconstruction era while emphasizing original student research in local sources.<br><br><strong>Anticipated Terms Offered:</strong> Offered periodically<br><br></div>		</td>
